{"batchSize":3,"level":"info","message":"Upsert batch:","sampleVector":{"id":"2e6fc46875c9d5ee4ae49efcec714713f2a1df0d73787aa9b32fac4142eddb2a","metadata":{"content":"Las Vegas Pool Masters - Your Pool Service Provider\nPool Maintenance Services\n### Pool Maintenance Services\n#### 1. How to Open a Pool\nWinter  is  over,  and  spring  is  finally  here.  Temperatures  are  rising.  The  sun  is  shining.  A  dip  in  the\npool sounds great! But don't jump in quite yet! \nIf your pool has been closed all winter, you'll need to do a little prep work to get your pool ready for\nanother season of fun. Don't worry though. \nOpening a pool is easy with these steps:\n- Step 1: Clean up debris and check for wear and tear.\n- Step 2: Inventory your pool chemicals.\n- Step 3: Remove the cover and clean it.\n- Step 4: Inspect the pool for damage or wear.\n- Step 5: Fill the pool to the proper water level.\n- Step 6: Turn on the pool filter and test the water.\n#### 2. How to Close a Pool For Winter\nAs cold weather approaches, it's time to start winterizing your swimming pool. Here's a quick guide:\n- Step 1: Balance your water chemistry.\n- Step 2: Add a shock treatment.\n- Step 3: Remove and clean pool equipment.\nPage 101","documentId":"67504b8e714ae2e95b66badc","pageNumber":"1","source":"Las_Vegas_Pool_Services.pdf","sourceType":"document"},"values":[0.04810173,0.026692059,-0.009550981,-0.034682333,-0.01875514,0.025131354,-0.0054891463,-0.007956928,-0.029720094,-0.009204159,-0.010758193,0.03871082,-0.007163236,0.0054091103,0.013712862,-0.026558666,0.018648425,-0.0037783736,0.0029096478,-0.000086757944,-0.017221114,0.01562039,0.0003213952,-0.020382542,-0.017194435,-0.019902324,0.011385144,-0.0063428655,-0.03638977,0.0023477273,0.0141530605,-0.02499796,-0.029106483,-0.008610557,-0.0047187987,0.0056358795,0.0014931746,-0.023477273,0.025131354,-0.021916568,0.017341167,0.009284195,0.00095126306,0.010571443,-0.0074900505,0.014513223,-0.011498528,-0.010297986,-0.034468904,0.0114